            <script is:inline>window.__HIGHLIGHTS_DATA__={"total":4160,"highlights":[{"id":1024620803,"text":"长期用 Claude Code 或 Codex 写项目的人，真该把 Trellis 装上试试。\n\n说它是现在最接近\"让 AI 记住你项目\"的方案，不算夸张。\n\n很多人写着写着觉得 AI \n\n!","title":"Tweets From 卡牌大师崔斯特","author":"@cuisitekp on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/cuisitekp/status/2065059643597160911"},{"id":1023754858,"text":"卧槽，这个应用火了🔥 \n还没有 Copy to China 吗👀\n\n这是一个很棒的病毒式传播应用创意！\n\n基本上是通过你在城市里走动来解锁虚拟地图上的区域。","title":"Tweets from Cell 细胞","author":"@cellinlab on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/cellinlab/status/2063876195825938792"},{"id":1023718133,"text":"给大家一些 /goal 的用例，防止 token 用不完\n\n1/ 产品说明文档\n\n基于当前 commit 的产品功能，运行真实 App / 模拟器 / 使用 CDP 进行页面检查和截图，产出一份面向普通用户的产品说明文档。","title":"Tweets From Hwang","author":"@hwwaanng on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/hwwaanng/status/2063824787743396242"},{"id":1023718131,"text":"Approve agent permissions without opening app.","title":"Tweets From Lody","author":"@lody_ai on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/lody_ai/status/2064162435444167055"},{"id":1023439731,"text":"Hallmark v1.1 is out 🎉\n\nThe open source design skill for beautiful UIs. Now with new themes, better designs, more AI slop detectors, and a new mode to drastically redesign apps.\n\nHere's what's new:\n\n◆ 4 new themes: Carnival, Lumen, Hum, and Cobalt\n◆ Better design: sharper hero","title":"Tweets From Hassan El Mghari","author":"@nutlope on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/nutlope/status/2062226108154618268"},{"id":1023439730,"text":"","title":"Tweets From Addy Osmani","author":"@addyosmani on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/addyosmani/status/2059844244907696186"},{"id":1022470483,"text":"太牛批了，某大厂内网的万字长文。核心项目组员工，在离职前的长篇吐槽，里面出现好几位高管名字。\n\n从见证 AI 立项，到 300 万日活，最后因管理者、员工、文化矛盾等问题，成为项目最后一位走的人。\n\n \n\n!\n\n!","title":"Tweets From AB Kuai.Dong","author":"@_FORAB on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/_FORAB/status/2062820205773152725"},{"id":1022181671,"text":"你们在设计 APP 图标的时候，考虑过一个 40 多岁老男人的感受吗？😂 @libapi_  @yetone \n\n!","title":"Tweets From Laogui","author":"@laogui on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/laogui/status/2062156091174297730"},{"id":1022181670,"text":"中午刷到一个有意思的 repo。LiteLLM 团队搞了个 self-hosted 的 agent 编排平台，把 Claude Code、Codex、Hermes 这些 coding agent 统一管理，还能在隔离沙箱里跑。核心是用一个 harness 抽象层，切换 agent 就跟换模型一样简单。自带 UI 和","title":"Tweets From 恒星","author":"@vintcessun on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/vintcessun/status/2062377804877197385"},{"id":1022000710,"text":"一早刷到一个repo，点很实在——coding agents进仓库后经常瞎改代码，因为没有项目上下文。它用一套文档结构和 agent shim，给 agents 提供“操作手册”：产品契约、风险分类、验证期望，本质上是在仓库层面装了个操作系统。Rust CLI 一键安装，支持合并更新，适合需要让 agents","title":"Tweets From 恒星","author":"@vintcessun on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/vintcessun/status/2061999562303435134"},{"id":1021016125,"text":"Codex做网页设计开发的正确打开方式：内置的Build Web Apps插件\n\n该插件包含设计、ui组件、测试验收等一系列网页开发skills，直接在官方插件市场下载即可配置\n\n下面是我用该插件做的世界杯主题网站，历史感拉满了","title":"Tweets From Sac","author":"@Saccc_c on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/Saccc_c/status/2061037491625357331"},{"id":1020627079,"text":"🤯一个控制 AI 航拍镜头的新玩法！\n直接在图片上画线， 让 AI 按红线生成无人机镜头💥\n\n我做了一段广州中轴线 FPV 航拍：\n低空穿过花城广场 → 贴楼拔高 → 穿楼顶结构 → 绕楼俯冲 → 掠过珠江 → 冲向小蛮腰 → 绕塔上升\n\n城市航拍、景区穿越、商业地产、楼宇宣传片…全都能这么玩！","title":"Tweets From Larus Canus","author":"@MrLarus on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/MrLarus/status/2060268998932000987"},{"id":1020617098,"text":"Built a pottery app today, where your real hands throw virtual clay 🏺\n\nHand tracking  > clay deformation > real-time physics\n\nNo controller. No stylus. Just hands.\n\nEverything built within @omma_ai + threejs\nModel of the puppet hand: credit to LiamVandeWouwer (SketchFab)","title":"Tweets From Joseph Azar","author":"@parazar on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/parazar/status/2060407652870500767"},{"id":1020476405,"text":"Claude Code 推出 Dynamic Workflows：\n从「一个 agent 干到底」升级到「agent 自己当项目经理 + 调度层」，标杆案例是 Bun Zig → Rust 迁移！\n\n让 Claude Code 根据任务现场生成编排脚本，在单次会话里启动 数十到数百个并行 subagent，并在结果交付前做  \n\n!","title":"Tweets From Meng Shao","author":"@shao__meng on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/shao__meng/status/2060157352612130821"},{"id":1020149733,"text":"We are cooked.\n\nAI can fake crowd size now 💀\n\nNothing is real anymore.","title":"Tweets From Min Choi","author":"@minchoi on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/minchoi/status/2059651369796083884"},{"id":1019756542,"text":"WTF？！这彻底改变了图像生成领域！PrismML 刚刚发布了 Binary 和 Ternary Bonsai Image 4B！\n\n没错，1-bit 扩散模型来了。模型大小只有约 3GB（相比之下，FLUX.2 Klein 4B 有 16GB）。\n\n最令人震惊的是？它可以完全在你的浏览器中本地运行。现在就可以试试👇","title":"Tweets From Huangserva","author":"@servasyy_ai on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/servasyy_ai/status/2059428034449756252"},{"id":1019726097,"text":"藏师傅的小红书图文排版 Skill 预览\n\n完全靠 HTML 和实拍图片，不会被标注 AI\n\nAI 会去高质量图片网站帮你寻找对应的主题图片，让你的图文告别只有生硬文字的尴尬情况  \n\n!","title":"Tweets From Op7418","author":"@op7418 on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/op7418/status/2059176154125480426"},{"id":1019473072,"text":"彭博消息，中国正在限制阿里巴巴、DeepSeek 等民营企业中，从事先进、战略性 AI 工作的顶尖专业人士出境。这些人在出国前，需要先获得相关部门批准。\n\n被通知对象，可能还包括 AI 领域创业公司的创始人、研究人员和高管。此举发生在 Manus 事件之后。 \n\n!","title":"Tweets From AB Kuai.Dong","author":"@_FORAB on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/_FORAB/status/2059220196263616828"},{"id":1019171841,"text":"兄弟们，Hyper3D 又放大招了\n\n这次是真的猛...\n\nRodin Gen-2.5发布：\n\n最强 3D 生成模型\n4 秒生成百万面模型\n全球首个千万面级3D生成\n\n在模型细节上，连毛孔、皮肤微结构这种级别的细节都能还原...\n\n原生贴图纹理，严格对齐几何，涉及到衣物质感和缝线等微小纹理正确，细节和对齐做到正确平衡。","title":"Tweets From 小互","author":"@xiaohu on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/xiaohu/status/2058779268247867848"},{"id":1019171840,"text":"为什么 AI 总是写不好 UI，总是看着很廉价很丑？\n\n 《Refactoring UI》第一章，Start with a feature, not a layout\n\n这一点上，目前的 Agent 就做不太到，包括 claude-design 等框架 \n\n!","title":"Tweets From Yeuoly","author":"@Yeuoly1 on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/Yeuoly1/status/2058858478975041658"},{"id":1018731475,"text":"这谁顶得住啊，\n日本服装巨头ZOZO，\n把他们内部搞服装虚拟试穿的顶级物理引擎\nppf-contact-solver（接触求解器）直接开源了！\n\n做虚拟时尚、数字服装、\n电影特效、甚至游戏物理的，\n这波福利直接白嫖顶级工业级工具啊！\n\n这玩意儿专治","title":"Tweets From HankAI","author":"@hank_aibtc on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/hank_aibtc/status/2058382186521526334"},{"id":1018731473,"text":"卧槽，😱GitHub上刚挖到的神器map3d，基于OpenStreetMap，你在网页上框选一个区域，它就能自动把真实的建筑物、道路数据抓下来，一键渲染成自带高度的3D城市模型！\n\n🚀最狠的是还能直接导出GLB文件，塞进Blender或游戏引擎里当资产！","title":"Tweets From 比特币橙子Trader","author":"@oragnes on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/oragnes/status/2058383530535817375"},{"id":1018731471,"text":"Codex でトップビューの画像から、3Dモデルに変換を試す\n\n「room.pngを元に、ローポリボクセルの教室を作って。\nVite + TypeScript + Three.js。\nテクスチャを $imagegen で生成して貼り付けて。」  \n\n!","title":"Tweets From 布留川英一 / Hidekazu Furukawa","author":"@npaka123 on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/npaka123/status/2058031349878194515"},{"id":1018690950,"text":"Thanks to the community report, we recently identified a PR  that attempted to solve a non-existent issue and was submitted as part of a “PR training” workflow for resume building.\n\nThe contributor involved has been banned from the vLLM community.\n\nThis \n\n!","title":"Tweets From vLLM","author":"@vllm_project on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/vllm_project/status/2058358072020779391"},{"id":1018425926,"text":"图片 3秒变完整 3D资产开源神器\n\n\n\n这就是 TRELLIS.2，微软官方开源的4B参数原生3D生成模型！直接干翻所有传统3D建模工具：扔一张任意图片进去，3秒出高分辨率带纹理、可商用3D资产，直接生成 GLB文件 + 完整 PBR  \n\n!","title":"Tweets From 币世王","author":"@0xKingsKuan on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/0xKingsKuan/status/2057416449292198303"},{"id":1018401081,"text":"11pm, in bed, vibecoding a duck on a plane as a meeting reminder.\n\nWe’re so back 🦆","title":"Tweets From Tom | Ooble Studio","author":"@tomboutin_ on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/tomboutin_/status/2057340078062817328"},{"id":1018321573,"text":"Lottie 友情提醒：GitHub README 可以内嵌动画 SVG。（Lottie 就是用来做动画的。）","title":"Tweets From Cat Chen","author":"@CatChen on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/CatChen/status/2057670547379740901"},{"id":1018321572,"text":"Most devs don't realize their GitHub can do THIS 👇\n\nYes, GitHub renders animations in READMEs.\nDrop your favorite GitHub repo that needs some animation love! We'll animate them.","title":"Tweets From LottieFiles","author":"@LottieFiles on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/LottieFiles/status/2057280288997384685"},{"id":1017980737,"text":"最近做了一个小小的 3D 个人主页。\n\n它不是普通作品集，而是一个可以慢慢逛的作品广场：你会操纵一只披风小猫，去看展板、听小电台、进马戏影院，也会遇到一只叫尼卡的导览猫。\n\n最近项目太忙，还没来得及继续细修，先把目前版本发出来。等忙完之后我再回来慢慢更新。\n\n在线体验： \n\n!","title":"Tweets From Ring Hyacinth","author":"@ring_hyacinth on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/ring_hyacinth/status/2057413771891773803"},{"id":1016739738,"text":"又一个开源的 Agent IDE：ORCA\n\n优势是直接提供iOS和安装移动客户端，支持多账号切换（比如多ChatGPT订阅），Token消耗、5小时重置显示。\n\n也是检测电脑里装好的各种Cli，比如Claude Code CLI、Codex CLI、Gemini CLI、Hermes、OpenClaw等。\n\n支持目录和文件拖拽对话，内置Markdown预览渲染。 \n\n!\n\n!\n\n!\n\n!","title":"Tweets from 向阳乔木","author":"@vista8 on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/vista8/status/2056271703203033118"},{"id":1016739736,"text":"等了两个月 @TencentAI_News  终于发布了 Ardot，怎么还把域名改了😂","title":"Tweets From Ding","author":"@dingyi on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/dingyi/status/2056286154786586730"},{"id":1016555190,"text":"我现在都懒得用 tmux 了，直接用  或  更方便，适合懒人。","title":"Tweets From Ding","author":"@dingyi on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/dingyi/status/2055528179830571472"},{"id":1015993590,"text":"喔艹？！ 微信读书 \n官方居然出了一个 Skill！\n\n把微信读书里常用能力基本度封装了：\n\n支持搜索书籍、查看书架、阅读统计、笔记划线、热门划线、书评、推荐好书，甚至可以拼接深度链接，直接跳回微信读书 App。\n\n（需要更新到 10.1.1\n\nskill 地址放评论区了👉 \n\n!","title":"Tweets from Cell 细胞","author":"@cellinlab on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/cellinlab/status/2055267224894542179"},{"id":1015814143,"text":"handoff 最近用的越来越多了，\n是目前我最高频使用的 skill 了，发现 Codex 上下文一长，反应速度明显下降的非常厉害，都不是界面卡顿，而是返回的速度，当然本身 GPT 模型本身上下文和其他相比比较小，所以对于长任务，到差不多 70% - 80% 我都会用 handoff","title":"Tweets From Viking","author":"@vikingmute on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/vikingmute/status/2054843346070503693"},{"id":1015814142,"text":"Both the iOS and macOS versions of SubList app have been released. You might need to wait a moment for the CDN to sync the new version.\nThis is how it looks on macOS.  \n\n!\n\n!\n\n!","title":"Tweets From Lex Tang","author":"@lexrus on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/lexrus/status/2054732003812212837"},{"id":1015166144,"text":"恐怖！用家Wi-Fi就能知道隔壁墙后的人在干什么！\n开源项目 RuView 在GitHub已经冲到 5万+星，直接炸了！\n\n完全不用摄像头，也不用戴任何设备，就靠家里普通的WiFi信号，就能穿墙透视：\n\n- 隔壁有几个人、在哪个位置、是走路还是躺着，全看得见\n- 实时看人体姿态（17个关键点）\n-","title":"Tweets From 开发者Hailey","author":"@IndieDevHailey on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/IndieDevHailey/status/2054386235867812240"},{"id":1014588954,"text":"kaomoji generator for when (ಥ﹏ಥ) isn't specific enough","title":"Tweets From Celine 🍓","author":"@celinekeomany on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/celinekeomany/status/2053653602057461877"},{"id":1014160993,"text":"Fun interactive science app ideas | Part 3\n\nPlayed around with generating 3D biological structures and made an app to explore them interactively\n\nUI Design\nGPT Images 2\n\nCode\nGemini 3.1 Pro\n\nMore demos ↓","title":"Tweets From Dilum Sanjaya","author":"@DilumSanjaya on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/DilumSanjaya/status/2053155739389378849"},{"id":1014160992,"text":"你问别人怎么做的，我给你默默做好了@CuiMao\n在线玩：\nGithub：","title":"Tweets From Gorden Sun","author":"@Gorden_Sun on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/Gorden_Sun/status/2052680167764689318"},{"id":1013073078,"text":"Codex做视频，简直太丝滑了！\n\n下载Codex，安装HyperFrames 插件，然后告诉它你要什么就可以生成了。\n\n我就说了一下「帮我生成一个鸡蛋的营养价值的视频」\n\n5分钟就生成了这种质量的宣传片...  \n\n全程我只需要点确认就可以了，做出来很完整，傻子都会做那种······","title":"Tweets From 潦草文子","author":"@Eejoylove on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/Eejoylove/status/2051966294833131745"},{"id":1013002346,"text":"Codex 最强剪辑插件 HyperFrames 视频版教程来了\n\n轻松学会后，一小时手搓任何视频，闲鱼挂单月入过万不是梦","title":"Tweets From Sac","author":"@Saccc_c on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/Saccc_c/status/2051959327557034478"},{"id":1012835086,"text":"卧槽！我必须单方面宣布 Codex 已经成为我的挚爱！😍\n\n今天早上打开电脑，发现 Codex 昨晚自己给我跑了一批图。\n\n🥳有几张真的开始有那种“相册里翻到的生活切片”的感觉了：糊的、歪的、手抖的、构图不完美，但情绪是对的。\n\n我本来只是想试一下在 Codex \n\n!","title":"Tweets From MapleShaw","author":"@msjiaozhu on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/msjiaozhu/status/2050424438001385678"},{"id":1012491798,"text":"每一种文化都会造就反映其最深层焦虑的英雄。","title":"科技爱好者周刊（第 394 期）：第二次 Api 开放浪潮","author":"阮一峰的网络日志","date":"2026.05.05","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01kqvbrqqvd86hnn4hpp1h2rx3"},{"id":1012286589,"text":"学习这个用 Anime.js 的  scrambleText  做了一个文字切换滚动的特效\n\n让 Codex 重新设计和整理了一下，支持各种字符 blocks / symbols / numbers / braille ，真的好帅啊，特别适合 geek 风网站的标题滚动效果\n\n之后准备封装成一个 npm","title":"Tweets From Viking","author":"@vikingmute on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/vikingmute/status/2051296619199598688"},{"id":1012148764,"text":"想起《人生切割术》美剧中主角在公司里每天对着电脑做着无意义的数据分类和清洗，这很像我最近几个月使用 AI 的感受，明明 Agent 把自己的许多时间从手写代码中解脱出来了，效率和产出也数十倍地提升，但并不像自己原本设想的那样，在等待的时间里可以去阅读、运动或是晒晒太阳，而是常常会无意义地在各个项目间切换自己头脑的上下文，以至于明明没有太多有效思考，却异常疲惫。","title":"周报 #108 - Ai 与创作的困境","author":"pseudoyu@connect.hku.hk (pseudoyu)","date":"2026.05.04","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01kqs11eps163mh6ay9qrafad9"},{"id":1011967805,"text":"兄弟们，做App最痛苦的部分终于被AI干掉了，\nAnything刚刚上线了一个功能，\n一键生成设计师级别的App Store截图，\n\n15秒，从空白到4张完美适配规格的上架图，\n连App图标评分Get按钮都给你做好了，\n\n改文案只需要输一句话，点一下生成就完事，","title":"Tweets from 阿绎 AYi","author":"@AYi_AInotes on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/AYi_AInotes/status/2048033665544823085"},{"id":1011967804,"text":"全程使用 Codex + GPT-5.5 + agent-sprite-forge\n\n半天時間做出一款類寶可夢的戰國妖怪捕捉 RPG。\n包含：\n- 4 張地圖 (2道館+2場景地圖)\n- 16 種怪物，含進化型共 27 個型態\n- 御三家選擇、野外遇敵、道館挑戰、Boss 戰\n- 怪物捕捉、升級、進化、圖鑑、道具、補血點\n- 自動生成地圖、角色、怪物","title":"Tweets From 0xFunky","author":"@0x0funky on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/0x0funky/status/2048433528162193854"},{"id":1011967801,"text":"Claude Code 值得安装的几个skills都整理好了\n\n1、Claude Mem - 给 Claude 装记忆，不用重复描述需求\n\n2、Obsidian Skills - 让 Claude 真正理解你的上下文\n\n3、GSD - 让 Claude 真正干活，不是瞎扯\n\n4、LightRAG -  \n\n!","title":"Tweets From 無顏(💙,🧡)(🌸, 🌿).lens","author":"@WY_mask on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/WY_mask/status/2048537609308344658"},{"id":1011967796,"text":"Codex++ 直接开源 + 内置 iOS Simulator？这波操作直接把开发循环干碎了 🔥\n以后原型 native UI 再也不用切来切去 Xcode 了，效率起飞！\n自定义键盘快捷键这个 tweak 也太实用，我已经想好要加哪些快捷键了～\n开源了就该冲！@b_nnett 牛逼，PR 安排上\n仓库地址在这里：","title":"Tweets From Lifcc","author":"@mylifcc on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/mylifcc/status/2049795791645229178"},{"id":1011967790,"text":"最近刷到一个看起来没用但是很喜欢的项目：claude-receipts\n\n每次和 AI 聊完以后，就可以生成一张消费小票，可以打印出来，贴到墙上，看看当贴满的时候，你的项目到底做的怎么样？\n\n有种怪异的浪漫，如果不想纸质的，用 html 的电子版也行，但是感觉差点事。 \n\n!","title":"Tweets From Viking","author":"@vikingmute on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/vikingmute/status/2049853265966453114"},{"id":1011967789,"text":"OpenClaw 现在可以抓取任何网站而不被屏蔽——零机器人检测，原生绕过 Cloudflare，比 BeautifulSoup 快 774 倍。\n\n无需维护选择器。无需变通方案。只需数据。\n\n这是不公平的优势，而且完全开源。\n \n\n!","title":"Tweets From 摆烂程序媛","author":"@wanerfu on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/wanerfu/status/2050158295911137370"},{"id":1011967787,"text":"终于！历时 3 天打磨，来自日本、德国、巴西、韩国等朋友的支持 💪\n\n支持 72+ 图片和视频模板、 open-design 正式支持全模态设计！🔥\n\ngpt-image 2、seedance 2、免费的 hyperframes！\n\n推特上最顶级提示词、模板直接用，每个人都能用顶级图片做顶级的设计🔥\n\n关注进展 👉","title":"Tweets From Tom Huang","author":"@tuturetom on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/tuturetom/status/2050202245447168315"},{"id":1011967785,"text":"我天，这条真的有点超出预期！🤪\n\n中午发的 Codex Prompt Lab，到现在 7 个多小时已经 8w+ 浏览。\n\n很多人在问：这是不是很费钱？Plus 够不够？教程在哪？定时任务怎么做？\n\n我先说最关键的一点：目前我只是 OpenAI Plus，没有额外氪 API。这两天这么跑，基本还没碰到 5 小时重置的上限。  \n\n!","title":"Tweets From MapleShaw","author":"@msjiaozhu on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/msjiaozhu/status/2050542845409517878"},{"id":1009493156,"text":"@mrblock 是真的要起飛\n現在連game sprite都可以直接用這個skill搭配codex\n一個prompt完成了","title":"Tweets From 0xFunky","author":"@0x0funky on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/0x0funky/status/2047719053276701113"},{"id":1009493155,"text":"🚀 OpenAI 又放大招了！\n\nGPT-Image-2 直接整合進 Codex，現在開發者可以用自然語言 prompt，即時在遊戲運行中生成並替換紋理，完全不用重啟！\n\n看這款 2D 殭屍塔防遊戲演示：懸崖、地板隨便叫 AI 改，幾十秒內就更新完成，檔案直接被替換，開發效率直接爆炸 🔥","title":"Tweets From 區塊先生 🐡 ⚠️","author":"@mrblock on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/mrblock/status/2047710909616058682"},{"id":1009493154,"text":"built an interactive guide to teach you the basics of mahjong ! 🀄\n\nit includes rulesets from different regions (hk and taiwan for now) with a few interactive elements to illustrate mahjong concepts. more demos in thread, and a bit about the tools i used to build this.\n\nthe one","title":"Tweets From Emily Han","author":"@emilyhanyf on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/emilyhanyf/status/2047412753695174675"},{"id":1009493151,"text":"Codex 內建 Image2 是真有太好用了。\n\n我本來只是想測看看能不能生成 2D game sprite，結果發現Image2已經可以很穩地產出角色動作的 sprite sheet，然後就順手做了一個 Skill 可以一句prompt生成任何的 2D 動畫。\n\n從 prompt設計 → image gen  → sprite sheet → cleanup → transparent PNG →","title":"Tweets From 0xFunky","author":"@0x0funky on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/0x0funky/status/2047476333358584089"},{"id":1009493149,"text":"an incredibly cool app concept with literally no ui..\n\nwizard » @jayhxmo","title":"Tweets From Aurelien","author":"@Aurelien_Gz on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/Aurelien_Gz/status/2047759443631223030"},{"id":1008215537,"text":"","title":"Tweets From 野生程序园","author":"@akokoi1 on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/akokoi1/status/2045693939584516441"},{"id":1008143185,"text":"Here’s the app link:","title":"Tweets From Kr$na","author":"@krishdotdev on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/krishdotdev/status/2045965949145415689"},{"id":1007807419,"text":"it's okay to build useless features on weekends","title":"Tweets From Adi","author":"@drianlarde_main on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/drianlarde_main/status/2045400537424961709"},{"id":1005411652,"text":"The guy who built this just called it \"the Bloomberg Terminal for CLI agents.\"\n\nAfter one look at the demo, that's exactly right.\n\nMaestro is a native macOS app that runs up to 12 Claude Code sessions in a live grid, each isolated in its own git worktree, each reporting its \n\n!","title":"Tweets From Louis Gleeson","author":"@aigleeson on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/aigleeson/status/2042870542978683146"},{"id":1005346508,"text":"说实话，今天看到这个，我直接把手里所有其他AI记忆方案全停了🤩🤩🤩\n\nYC总裁Garry Tan，把自己天天在用的生产级AI Agent记忆系统，完整开源了\n\n这是他自己跑了很久的真实配置，管着10000+Markdown文件，3000+人物档案，13年的日历数据，5800条苹果笔记，还有所有的会议记录、原创想法  \n\n!","title":"Tweets from 阿绎 AYi","author":"@AYi_AInotes on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/AYi_AInotes/status/2042594916862431669"},{"id":1005341633,"text":"I am updating website for  \n\n!","title":"Tweets From Wiedy Mi","author":"@wiedymi on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/wiedymi/status/2042559712751947879"},{"id":1005341632,"text":"有人实在受够了与 Claude Code 反复来回地沟通，于是开发出了一种直接在屏幕上“涂鸦”的方法。Claude 渲染出一个预览界面……你只需圈出错误、添加箭头或写下注释。它是 100% 开源的，并且可以在本地运行。","title":"Tweets From Bill the Investor","author":"@billtheinvestor on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/billtheinvestor/status/2042677131990450515"},{"id":1005341631,"text":"You should be able to watch your agents work","title":"Tweets From John Bai","author":"@johnbai on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/johnbai/status/2042683615008412002"},{"id":1005273160,"text":"Claude Code 新增了一个叫 ultraplan 的功能：你在终端里发起一个规划任务，Claude 会在云端帮你起草实现方案，你在浏览器里审阅、批注、修改，满意之后选择在云端执行或者拉回本地终端执行。","title":"Tweets From 宝玉","author":"@dotey on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/dotey/status/2042675917927977084"},{"id":1005158803,"text":"兄弟们，今晚别再刷抖音消磨时间了\n\n这条 1 小时播客，专访 Claude Code 负责人。\n\n抽出一小时，沉下心来看完这套视频，你对 vibe-coding（氛围式编程）的理解，会超过 100 门付费课程。\n\n它能教会你自主搭建、自动化处理各类事务\n今晚认真学完的兄弟，明天醒来就会掌握一项","title":"Tweets From 看不懂的sol","author":"@DtDt666 on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/DtDt666/status/2042598697540948285"},{"id":1005150022,"text":"最贵缩放录屏软件Screen Studio，核心功能被Recordly复刻，完全免费开源！\n\n同时支持Mac/Windows/Linux。\n\n测试了下，比Screen Studio还轻便顺滑，立省1500+人民币啊？！\n\n下载地址和Github见评论区 \n\n!\n\n!","title":"Tweets from 向阳乔木","author":"@vista8 on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/vista8/status/2042046881635979312"},{"id":1005136513,"text":"A Bloomberg Terminal costs $30,000/yr and still can't do a fraction of what Perplexity Computer just launched today 💻\n\nIt now connects directly to your bank accounts, credit cards, loans, and brokerage accounts through Plaid. Your full financial picture, from monthly spending to","title":"Tweets From Josh Kale","author":"@JoshKale on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/JoshKale/status/2042301797868449858"},{"id":1005124699,"text":"The new AI-powered Google Finance is going global and shipping to 100+ countries… it’s a total reinvention of Google Finance with AI at the core 🚀🚀🚀\n\n+ AI-powered market research\n+ Advanced charting\n+ Live earnings calls\n+ Expanded real-time data\n\nTry it: \n\n!","title":"Tweets From Nick Fox","author":"@thefox on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/thefox/status/2041910855479259400"},{"id":1005106967,"text":"超すごいやん。。\n\nHeptabaseやExvalidrawみたいに、空間を使って、Agentの挙動を制御してる\n\nTerminal同士を、矢印で接続するというこの発想。。\n\nすごい","title":"Tweets From Hiroya Iizuka / 飯塚 浩也","author":"@0317_hiroya on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/0317_hiroya/status/2042379543139500051"},{"id":1005106955,"text":"this is kinda crazy\n\nbeen playing around with a new terminal app idea\n\norchestrate multiple terminals with an ai agent sidebar\n\nit's like having that giant wall of phones lol\n\nlemme know if you wanna try it","title":"Tweets From Wes Winder","author":"@weswinder on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/weswinder/status/2042456593539735658"},{"id":1004865370,"text":"有人用一帧标注图 + 一个很小的 YOLO nano 模型，就在传送带上做出了土豆计数器。\n\n不用大规模数据集，也不用重型基础设施。\n只用一帧，再配合 SAM 2 训练，就能在整段视频里稳定工作。\n\n工业场景里真正有用的 AI，很多时候就是这种形态。","title":"Tweets From Bill the Investor","author":"@billtheinvestor on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/billtheinvestor/status/2041935572806332418"},{"id":1004850086,"text":"我一直有拍小票的习惯，这两天鼓了一点劲儿，新 vibe 了一个小票搜集 App，自己用着挺开心的","title":"Tweets From DK","author":"@bulletonbible on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/bulletonbible/status/2042168517974429974"},{"id":1004850085,"text":"今天发现 Awesome Design MD 出了一个单独的网站了：\n这下安装就方便多了，不用在 Github 中拷贝了，只需要找到自己喜欢的 design 然后运行它们封装好的命令\nnpx getdesign@latest add XXX 就好了\n\n而且现在的 design.md","title":"Tweets From Viking","author":"@vikingmute on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/vikingmute/status/2042229353245978673"},{"id":1004850084,"text":"今天 GitHub 被一人顶十人 Agent军团彻底屠榜了🚀\n\n5 个星标暴增最狠的项目，专业拆解下！\n\n1.  camel-ai/owl \n\n多智能体协作框架，让专业化 Agent通过浏览器、终端、函数调用和 MCP工具实现无缝团队作战，GAIA 基准测试位居开源榜首，彻底解决单 Agent复杂任务易崩盘的痛点。 \n\n🔗 直达","title":"Tweets From GitTrend","author":"@GitTrend0x on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/GitTrend0x/status/2042063155485143279"},{"id":1004588157,"text":"Claude Code for Designers 免费课程。","title":"Tweets From Ding","author":"@dingyi on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/dingyi/status/2041637399651041602"},{"id":1004588156,"text":"用 Claude Code、Codex 写代码，Token 花了多少、费用怎么样，心里一直没个数，想看看每天的消耗情况还挺麻烦。\n\n可以安装 Agentic Metric 这个开源工具，相当于给它们装了个「资源监视器」，所有数据都在本地，不联网不上传。\n\n直接在终端里打开一个实时仪表盘，自动检测正在运行的智能体进程，Token \n\n!","title":"Tweets From GitHubDaily","author":"@GitHub_Daily on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/GitHub_Daily/status/2041727776731107545"},{"id":1004580959,"text":"画图 skill 开放出来了，欢迎使用","title":"Tweets From yofine.eth","author":"@yofine2js on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/yofine2js/status/2039368981178650694"},{"id":1004262246,"text":"Karpathy 前两天刚说“应该有人做这个”，\n\n兄弟们，48小时后就有人直接干出来了！\n\nGraphify 横空出世：\n\n✅ 指向任意文件夹  \n✅ 在 Claude Code 里输入 /graphify  \n✅ 自动生成完整知识图谱 + Obsidian vault + Wiki  \n✅ 支持 13 种代码语言 + PDF + 图片（Claude Vision）  \n✅ 查询 token \n\n!","title":"Tweets From Berryxia.AI","author":"@berryxia on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/berryxia/status/2041294530008494343"},{"id":1003957805,"text":"","title":"Tweets From 实践哥MinLi","author":"@MinLiBuilds on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/MinLiBuilds/status/2040580427916919180"},{"id":1003941581,"text":"今天 GitHub 被自我进化记忆性 Agent 屠榜了了 🚀\n\n5 个星标暴增最狠的项目，专业拆解下！\n\n1.  NousResearch/hermes-agent\n\n自我进化记忆 Agent，彻底解决传统Agent 一次忘光光的痛点，通过动态patch 机制让 AI伴随你成长，越用越懂你的黑历史和偏好\n\n🔗 直达","title":"Tweets From GitTrend","author":"@GitTrend0x on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/GitTrend0x/status/2040772348450910517"},{"id":1003941580,"text":"undo → summon it back from the rocks 🫴🪨","title":"Tweets From Bruce Cao","author":"@bruce_CQT on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/bruce_CQT/status/2040821526623392174"},{"id":1003881904,"text":"I have so much gratitude to people who wrote extremely complex software character-by-character. It already feels difficult to remember how much effort it really took.\n\nThank you for getting us to this point.","title":"Tweets From Sam Altman","author":"@sama on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/sama/status/2033935276079510011"},{"id":1003881903,"text":"传说中的DeepSeek天才少女、雷军千万年薪挖角的罗福莉也开始发推了。\n\n帖子里最生动的段落是关于她第一次使用复杂 Agent 脚手架的经历。她用的词是：orchestrated Context，编排过的上下文，我理解就是现在比较火的 Harness Engineering。","title":"Tweets From 宝玉","author":"@dotey on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/dotey/status/2034675747479064711"},{"id":1003881902,"text":"","title":"Tweets From Augment Code","author":"@augmentcode on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/augmentcode/status/2025993446633492725"},{"id":1003881900,"text":"Subagents are now available in Codex.\n\nYou can accelerate your workflow by spinning up specialized agents to:\n• Keep your main context window clean\n• Tackle different parts of a task in parallel\n• Steer individual agents as work unfolds","title":"Tweets From OpenAI Developers","author":"@OpenAIDevs on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/OpenAIDevs/status/2033636701848174967"},{"id":1003881899,"text":"别再手动学习 harness 。直接使用 harness skills。\n这个harness-creator技能能够帮大家一键生成、评估和优化AI agent的harness系统，自动搭好AGENTS.md、feature list、session连续性和验证流程，也能诊断现有项目的薄弱环节，集中提升agent的可靠性和多轮记忆。\n \n\n!\n\n!","title":"Tweets From Sanbu GenAI","author":"@sanbuphy on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/sanbuphy/status/2040253118647316950"},{"id":1003881898,"text":"every skeleton screen you've ever hand-coded is a waste of time\n\nyou're literally measuring padding and guessing widths to build a worse version of a layout that already exists in your DOM\n\nso I made a package that just reads the real one","title":"Tweets From Goodfuture","author":"@0xGoodfuture on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/0xGoodfuture/status/2039818750568878245"},{"id":1003881896,"text":"今天 GitHub 被被 Agent 军团彻底屠榜了🚀\n\n5 个星标暴增最狠的项目，专业拆解下！\n\n1.  MervinPraison/PraisonAI\n\n低代码多代理框架，把 LLM 直接变成你的 24/7 AI员工团队，支持规划、研究、编码、交付，还能跨 Telegram/Discord/WhatsApp 无缝交接、带记忆RAG 和 100+模型。\n\n🔗 直达","title":"Tweets From GitTrend","author":"@GitTrend0x on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/GitTrend0x/status/2040238756306067650"},{"id":1003881895,"text":"兄弟们，原来蒸馏如此的见效快！\n难怪大厂都热衷于此哈哈哈😂\n\nApple Research（苹果研究院）刚刚发布了一篇“超级简单却效果炸裂”的论文，标题直接叫《Embarrassingly Simple Self-Distillation Improves Code Generation》（尴尬的简单自蒸馏就能大幅提升代码生成能力）。\n\n论文核心发现（Simple  \n\n!","title":"Tweets From Berryxia.AI","author":"@berryxia on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/berryxia/status/2040570633042690194"},{"id":1003881894,"text":"superpower 和 gstack 还没玩够\n\n又来个 Google 大佬的最佳实践。\n\n学不动了","title":"Tweets From 关木","author":"@ZeroZ_JQ on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/ZeroZ_JQ/status/2040719922071056515"},{"id":1003881892,"text":"I've been playing with React Native WebGPU recently and it's really flipping my perspective on animations.","title":"Tweets From Enzo Manuel Mangano","author":"@reactiive_ on Twitter","date":"","url":"https://x.com/reactiive_/status/2040511285998313827"},{"id":1003847249,"text":"在一个信息收藏极其廉价的时代，我门缺的不是存下来的仓库，而是可以被你愉悦地读进去、被 AI 使用、能发挥价值的思考。","title":"回归阅读，开放连接｜Cubox 收藏类型变更公告","author":"Todd","date":"2026.04.06","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01knhc16f05zcc89x3xm9rc6tw"},{"id":996341237,"text":"时间是唯一不可再生的资源。AI 大模型是目前我所知的最便宜的赚取额外时间的方式。不要太看重 AI 大模型的订阅费","title":"科技爱好者周刊（第 388 期）：测试是新的护城河","author":"阮一峰的网络日志","date":"2026.03.14","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01kkn6vr7jdykdv742kw2hsmkt"},{"id":991620918,"text":"维特根斯坦曾写道：当眼睛看见美的事物，手就想把它画下来。","title":"当 Ai 比你更有品味","author":"南山居氪","date":"2026.02.25","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01kjaqy5e4ztgfcdv351v6dhm3"},{"id":991620910,"text":"我们以什么方式为这个世界创造价值？\n\nIvan 提出了一个精巧的框架，将价值拆解为三个维度：\n\n1.  能力——我们拥有的技能与知识。你能生火吗？能计算火箭的飞行轨迹吗？能搭建一个网站吗？能从一群幼儿园小朋友中揪出偷饼干的那个？\n2.  品味——我们的价值观与偏好。更吸引你的是新艺术运动的有机曲线，还是包豪斯的冷峻功能？更触动你的是眼前一个人切身的苦难，还是可能波及未来千万人的潜在危害？你更看重一个惊艳的终点，还是一条优雅的途径？\n3.  行动力——我们的意志与驱力。即便知道怎么做，我们是否有足够的动力去做？是否在乎到愿意起身行动？三者协力，决定了我们如何真正创造贡献：能力界定我们能做什么，品味指引我们想做什么，行动力决定我们会做什么。","title":"当 Ai 比你更有品味","author":"南山居氪","date":"2026.02.25","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01kjaqxtsaqdq3rw34ashc9sr5"},{"id":988629180,"text":"不要学着像机器一样思考，那是自寻死路。\n\n去读诗，去谈恋爱，去搞人际博弈，去重拾那份脆弱但珍贵的共情。\n\n只要我们还拥有那份「不被算法翻译」的灵魂，我们便依然是这个星球唯一的牧星者。","title":"文科生年薪72万美元！Anthropic总裁预警：逻辑已死，ASI不养码农","author":"算法与数学之美","date":"2026.02.16","url":"https://readwise.io/open/988629180"},{"id":988527153,"text":"没有核心价值，就不要提前抢跑","title":"#334 没有核心价值，就不要提前抢跑","author":"cubox.pro","date":"2026.02.16","url":"https://readwise.io/open/988527153"},{"id":904030458,"text":"奢侈品的价值，从来不是孤立地存在于商品本身，而是存在于“商品”和“使用场景”的强绑定之中。","title":"Labubu 哪有泡沫？","author":"评论尸","date":"2025.06.17","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jxz8sq9jstxh3raq4656eftz"},{"id":904030342,"text":"因此，在 Labubu，以及类似的炒作盘中，泡沫本身就是使用价值。","title":"Labubu 哪有泡沫？","author":"评论尸","date":"2025.06.17","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jxz8pt6pcbjans8x8fnsxfrp"},{"id":904023575,"text":"这种分析，看起来数据详实，逻辑严密，充满了理性的光辉。在任何一个商学院的课堂上，这都是一份可以拿高分的标准答案。但它犯了一个根本性的错误：用分析“制造业”的尺子，去度量一个“宗教”的价值。\n\n这就像一百年前的马车夫，用“马匹的食量与行进里程”模型来分析福特 T 型车，最后得出结论：这玩意儿不吃草，光喝油，还要修，不靠谱，是骗局。\n\n当一个物种发生变异，演化出新的生存逻辑时，用旧的生态位去评估它，本身就是一种“搏蠢”。","title":"Labubu 哪有泡沫？","author":"评论尸","date":"2025.06.17","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jxz771fgv3mxqb9bq3f35nen"},{"id":902591290,"text":"Claude Code: Best practices for agentic coding","title":"Claude Code Best Practices \\ Anthropic","author":"anthropic.com","date":"2025.06.13","url":"https://readwise.io/open/902591290"},{"id":902591289,"text":"Claude Code is My Computer","title":"Claude Code Is My Computer | Peter Steinberger","author":"steipete.me","date":"2025.06.13","url":"https://readwise.io/open/902591289"},{"id":902591288,"text":"PandaWiki 是一款 AI 大模型驱动的开源知识库搭建系统，帮助你快速构建智能化的 产品文档、技术文档、FAQ、博客系统，借助大模型的力量为你提供 AI 创作、AI 问答、AI 搜索 等能力。","title":"PandaWiki","author":"github.com","date":"2025.06.13","url":"https://readwise.io/open/902591288"},{"id":902496726,"text":"人们总是喜欢新东西，读书喜欢读新出版的书，听歌喜欢听新歌。\n\n据统计，美国2024年流媒体音乐一共播放了1.4万亿次，其中近50%是2020年至2024年期间发行的歌曲，近80%是2010年或之后发行的歌曲。歌越老，听的人越少。美联社","title":"科技爱好者周刊（第 352 期）：Bug 追踪系统的正确样子","author":"阮一峰的网络日志","date":"2025.06.13","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jxkybf8tqw8cce3wvdzk22s4"},{"id":902491761,"text":"赞声与骂声，都不要在意，而要在乎自己能不能做好。把自己做好，就没有问题。","title":"科技爱好者周刊（第 352 期）：Bug 追踪系统的正确样子","author":"阮一峰的网络日志","date":"2025.06.13","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jxkx331jhe6041fz55dhavbc"},{"id":899843021,"text":"!","title":"棱镜通讯 No.114 海蒂·拉玛（Hedy Lamarr）","author":"太隐","date":"2025.06.06","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jx30pvmxq13ryyktpmaqnsmn"},{"id":899842814,"text":"社会总想定义你是什么人，但真正的自由在于拒绝被定义","title":"棱镜通讯 No.114 海蒂·拉玛（Hedy Lamarr）","author":"太隐","date":"2025.06.06","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jx30n11hr0yg2zps3bmmc35r"},{"id":899664360,"text":"AI是一片肥沃的土壤，而你的生命体验，你的价值观，你的想法和创意才是最根本的根系。","title":"即梦图片3.0又重磅更新，这可能是对普通人最有用的一次。","author":"Bookmark / Raindrop.io","date":"2025.06.06","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jx1wgsxp0560d93np44se24y"},{"id":899664349,"text":"生活是设计的起源地，而设计归根结底是对我们生活的发言。","title":"即梦图片3.0又重磅更新，这可能是对普通人最有用的一次。","author":"Bookmark / Raindrop.io","date":"2025.06.06","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jx1wgj84n1m3azw540y04d2k"},{"id":899663385,"text":"我们生命中最美好的时刻，并非是那些接受给予、放松享受的时刻，而是那些为了完成一件困难而有价值的事情，自愿将身心发挥到极限的时刻。","title":"科技爱好者周刊（第 351 期）：GitHub Issues（几乎）是最好的笔记应用","author":"阮一峰的网络日志","date":"2025.06.06","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jx1wcccq8epefhzr0y3r1y4h"},{"id":899474591,"text":"好奇心旺盛、喜欢反思、喜欢挑战困难的人，往往会从独处中得到更多的满足感，从而也就更喜欢独处。","title":"喜欢独处，其实是一种难得的天赋","author":"Bookmark / Raindrop.io","date":"2025.06.05","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jx0dybsa42kw0djspf0t8vkg"},{"id":899474539,"text":"面对面的社交，需要你付出非常多的精力 —— 你需要保持情绪饱满，时刻去接收和响应对方的信息，并一直维持这种状态和情绪。","title":"喜欢独处，其实是一种难得的天赋","author":"Bookmark / Raindrop.io","date":"2025.06.05","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jx0dxhspzn3kktzr6pwrdprc"},{"id":897839113,"text":"每个人的心灵深处都有一座花冢，埋藏着比寂寞更凄美却又不为外人道的情感。","title":"世间的小儿女","author":"陈慧","date":"2025.05.18","url":"https://readwise.io/open/897839113"},{"id":897839112,"text":"小孩子真是一把尺子，一刻不停在长大，以此度量着大人们的年华飞逝。","title":"世间的小儿女","author":"陈慧","date":"2025.05.18","url":"https://readwise.io/open/897839112"},{"id":897839111,"text":"人总是擅长把苦难熬成蜜糖，再把自己泡进去。","title":"思考就是我的抵抗","author":"[英]弗吉尼亚·伍尔夫","date":"2025.06.01","url":"https://readwise.io/open/897839111"},{"id":896500102,"text":"在未来，纯粹由人类手工创作的文章、绘画、音乐，或许会像前些年受追捧的“老师傅手炒茶”一样，成为一种稀缺的、带有某种情怀和文化附加值的“奢侈品”。它们的存在，更多的是满足一小部分人对“原真性”的极致追求，普通大众或许难以企及，也未必真正需要。","title":"为什么人们喜欢鉴定 Ai？","author":"评论尸","date":"2025.05.30","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jwfva3ajc61cqzmy7a5nznan"},{"id":896500094,"text":"一篇文字、一幅画作、一段旋律，其价值将不再取决于它的“出身”，而是取决于它能否提供真正的信息增益，能否引发深刻的情感共鸣，能否在实用层面解决用户的问题。质量、真实性、以及对消费者的实际效用，将重新成为衡量内容好坏的黄金标准。","title":"为什么人们喜欢鉴定 Ai？","author":"评论尸","date":"2025.05.30","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jwfv9gwhqkcbtdwzfb3g8t4j"},{"id":896500058,"text":"当机器的笔触与人类的灵感融为一体，难分彼此之时，我们对内容的评判标准，或许将不得不回归到那些更朴素、更实在的维度","title":"为什么人们喜欢鉴定 Ai？","author":"评论尸","date":"2025.05.30","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jwfv8z74h0x82taf3d4ttm3n"},{"id":896039473,"text":"程序构建是一个降低熵的过程，而程序维护则是熵增的过程。 即便是最高效的维护，也只能延缓系统滑向无法修复的过时状态。\n\n—— Fred Brooks，《人月神话》（1975）","title":"Ai 会加速工程师的无能","author":"宝玉","date":"2025.05.29","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jwd9etg2h4dxnmjpqd0pnfn3"},{"id":896038769,"text":"AI带来的自信往往是以牺牲批判性思维为代价的。","title":"Ai 会加速工程师的无能","author":"宝玉","date":"2025.05.29","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jwd9cva23ekt0hzq7chpfycw"},{"id":895787437,"text":"“应无所住而生其心”","title":"Claude：拆书","author":"Bookmark / Raindrop.io","date":"2025.05.28","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jwbqc8y8qcwrkn4af77sytja"},{"id":895787376,"text":"自由不是能去任何地方，而是无论在哪里都能抵达自己。","title":"Claude：拆书","author":"Bookmark / Raindrop.io","date":"2025.05.28","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jwbqb9exdpw06sym18nz4vyd"},{"id":895787342,"text":"痛苦不是生活给你的，是你的头脑给你的。","title":"Claude：拆书","author":"Bookmark / Raindrop.io","date":"2025.05.28","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jwbqazfe5zwz6j5mpn2wffsg"},{"id":895787130,"text":"真实的思想是细腻流淌的，文字表达不仅要追求凝练，更要追求精确。所谓精确，不是指文字精彩，而是真诚，通过丰富的语言，捕捉那些内心深处不易察觉、模糊存在的想法。这个过程无法被 AI 简化，它也可以被称作「正念写作」。","title":"如何夺回失去的注意力？","author":"Bookmark / Raindrop.io","date":"2025.05.28","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jwbq9s70g4e0q5jyrmz1fmkk"},{"id":895786859,"text":"每个人就像一个接收装置，单改变信息输入的数量和质量是不够的，正念阅读的目标是先调谐好这个接收器本身，优化它的信息处理方式。我会用有限的个人经验来展示，只要多加练习，练习关注那些常被忽视但又至关重要的信息背面，我们就能减少被裹挟，在信息中更好地生活。","title":"如何夺回失去的注意力？","author":"Bookmark / Raindrop.io","date":"2025.05.28","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jwbq8j416gbbfxnjmqb6970v"},{"id":895786826,"text":"每个信息背后都有未被揭示的一面，正念阅读可以帮助把注意力放在我们阅读时发生的一切、包括阅读过程的情绪体验之上，而不仅仅是信息本身。","title":"如何夺回失去的注意力？","author":"Bookmark / Raindrop.io","date":"2025.05.28","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jwbq85bstt15dfef2ewacgb3"},{"id":895786542,"text":"我们被信息所塑造而成的自我，也决定了我们会如何对待我们的所见所闻","title":"如何夺回失去的注意力？","author":"Bookmark / Raindrop.io","date":"2025.05.28","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jwbq767y7c06f0nkf91dx4j0"},{"id":895786518,"text":"对信息的应对方式，未来将比信息本身更重要。","title":"如何夺回失去的注意力？","author":"Bookmark / Raindrop.io","date":"2025.05.28","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jwbq6jkaxjr1prgqfjn0hdka"},{"id":895786461,"text":"阅读本应该作为一种主动的思考活动存在，帮助我们抵抗情绪消耗，觉察到信息中的异样，进而改善我们对外的信息交流，但因为种种原因，它变得被动、成为了帮凶。我们不再选择去阅读，而是被阅读选择。","title":"如何夺回失去的注意力？","author":"Bookmark / Raindrop.io","date":"2025.05.28","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jwbq69gd49tjh7x518eb56t6"},{"id":895786340,"text":"现代的信息环境很擅长伪装，假装对我们有益，假装信息越多越好，好让我们沉浸其中。社交媒体设计的各种机制就是在利用这种情绪，从而进一步放大了危害。","title":"如何夺回失去的注意力？","author":"Bookmark / Raindrop.io","date":"2025.05.28","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jwbq5gg75xj6v4hxm1wtxqm2"},{"id":895786326,"text":"不要低估这种波动，它们悄悄地在我们的心里堆积成大山。几秒钟的信息输入，可能引发数天的情绪消耗，它持久、隐蔽、没有终结甚至无法暂停。作为社交动物，我们会通过他人、外界来判断和定义自己。在地球的所有生物中，也许只有人类会有这样的深刻体验吧，这既是一种天赋，又是一种诅咒。","title":"如何夺回失去的注意力？","author":"Bookmark / Raindrop.io","date":"2025.05.28","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jwbq585d3y2k3q3w4dg3j1nt"},{"id":895786294,"text":"在原始社会，人类的情绪波动通常来自引发生存危机的信号，这些情绪可以转化为巨大的行动力，避免灾难的发生，帮助生命延续。但现在呢？情绪的波动很少来自实质的生存挑战，而是转向了心理层面的认同，源于那些看似无害的碎片化的信息体验。","title":"如何夺回失去的注意力？","author":"Bookmark / Raindrop.io","date":"2025.05.28","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jwbq4gc9xp8y1k6afrqcpwfx"},{"id":895786256,"text":"阅读就是解读和理解世界，原来一切都有关阅读。","title":"如何夺回失去的注意力？","author":"Bookmark / Raindrop.io","date":"2025.05.28","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jwbq3gxkdcd31y6zw7jsdz1x"},{"id":895786221,"text":"我们是谁？我们应该如何定义自己？除了镜子面前的肉体，我们的情感、文化、思想，我们对信息的品味偏好，其实才真正塑造了我们的身份认同，它们一直在变化，也因此对我们自我认知的影响，远远超出了肉身的局限。","title":"如何夺回失去的注意力？","author":"Bookmark / Raindrop.io","date":"2025.05.28","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jwbq2td3zp4jfxrw77e6c8nr"},{"id":895785856,"text":"觉察、重构、创造，这三个策略逐步升级，是从无意识到有意识，到创造意识的过程。最初你什么都不用做，只需有心观察，看清楚环境；接下来，你重新组织信息，成为信息流的主人；最终你按捺不住激情，分享、写作，将阅读变成了自己的一部分，升华了一切。","title":"没有社交媒体的世界，会变得更好吗？","author":"Bookmark / Raindrop.io","date":"2025.05.28","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jwbpyafmkmbrz2pvd9skxrgk"},{"id":895785683,"text":"通过写作，你可以占有和塑造这个世界上的任何事物。当你生长出这样的塑造力，在阅读社交媒体时，你将不再被算法趁虚而入。","title":"没有社交媒体的世界，会变得更好吗？","author":"Bookmark / Raindrop.io","date":"2025.05.28","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jwbpy3wndh3fdhn45q0kr9tq"},{"id":895785466,"text":"对社交媒体、对聊天记录、对身边的一草一木记录想法。把自己置身于什么样的环境，就会有什么样的思考方式，善待自己脑海中的思绪。","title":"没有社交媒体的世界，会变得更好吗？","author":"Bookmark / Raindrop.io","date":"2025.05.28","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jwbpxrpzvg66dt6cbzbgmp8b"},{"id":890559589,"text":"“单点突破，逐步放大”，一开始尽量聚焦到只解决用户一个迫切的需求，这样验证起来也非常简单。解决的问题要一句话就可以说清楚，比如小米充电宝解决的问题就是“怎样获得大容量、质量可靠又便宜的充电宝”。","title":"小米创业思考","author":"雷军 徐洁云","date":"2025.04.07","url":"https://readwise.io/open/890559589"},{"id":890559588,"text":"决定不做什么跟决定做什么一样重要","title":"小米创业思考","author":"雷军 徐洁云","date":"2025.04.07","url":"https://readwise.io/open/890559588"},{"id":890559587,"text":"任由这样的“局部正循环”“野蛮生长”，往往并不能带来“全局正循环”，而是会指向一种近乎失控的状态。这里的关键问题就是，局部组织的行动方向与公司整体方向是否严格对齐？如果放任偏差，哪怕只是失之毫厘，最终也一定是谬以千里。","title":"小米创业思考","author":"雷军 徐洁云","date":"2025.04.07","url":"https://readwise.io/open/890559587"},{"id":890559586,"text":"要保持整体专注，就要进行目标分解和持续校验。分解和校验的过程，也是对能力体系的检验和指导过程。","title":"小米创业思考","author":"雷军 徐洁云","date":"2025.04.07","url":"https://readwise.io/open/890559586"},{"id":890559585,"text":"专注、极致、口碑、快，这就是我总结的互联网七字诀，也是我对互联网思维的高度概括。","title":"小米创业思考","author":"雷军 徐洁云","date":"2025.04.07","url":"https://readwise.io/open/890559585"},{"id":890559584,"text":"“三大铁律”分别为技术为本、性价比为纲、做最酷的产品。","title":"小米创业思考","author":"雷军 徐洁云","date":"2025.04.07","url":"https://readwise.io/open/890559584"},{"id":890559583,"text":"互联网作为技术工具，没有善恶对错，但互联网理想、精神和方法，从互联网出现的第一天开始，就是为了高效、透明、公平和普惠。","title":"小米创业思考","author":"雷军 徐洁云","date":"2025.03.19","url":"https://readwise.io/open/890559583"},{"id":890559582,"text":"说来也怪，这位诗人把宇宙掰开揉碎重组，却独独漏了人间的烟火气。","title":"思考就是我的抵抗","author":"[英]弗吉尼亚·伍尔夫","date":"2025.05.17","url":"https://readwise.io/open/890559582"},{"id":890559581,"text":"好的悲剧如同一颗腌透的橄榄，嚼得越久，苦涩中的回甘便愈发汹涌。","title":"思考就是我的抵抗","author":"[英]弗吉尼亚·伍尔夫","date":"2025.05.17","url":"https://readwise.io/open/890559581"},{"id":890559580,"text":"这是一种聪明的浅薄，而非深刻的智慧。","title":"思考就是我的抵抗","author":"[英]弗吉尼亚·伍尔夫","date":"2025.05.16","url":"https://readwise.io/open/890559580"},{"id":890559579,"text":"在纷繁复杂的世界中，作者以敏锐的洞察力和深刻的思考，为读者提供了丰富的文学体验和人生感悟，引导他们在思考中重塑自我，用思想抵抗平庸与荒诞。","title":"思考就是我的抵抗","author":"[英]弗吉尼亚·伍尔夫","date":"2025.05.15","url":"https://readwise.io/open/890559579"},{"id":890245678,"text":"P.S. idk when AGI is coming but Dia roasted me pretty hard the other day (attached). \n\nAnd I can say I never thought in a million years that my computer would make me laugh (never mind peer deep into my soul and insecurities). \n\nDed. \n\n!","title":"An Update on Our New AI...","author":"@joshm on Twitter","date":"2025.05.16","url":"https://twitter.com/joshm/status/1922639541829017817"},{"id":890245677,"text":"Dia & Browser Co aside that moment is here and it’s pretty remarkable.\n\nFive years ago saying Google Chrome & Search might be unseated felt wild. Now it feels inevitable.\n\nRoot for us, root against us I’m so pumped for this new internet & we’re giving it our all. Should be fun! \n\n!","title":"An Update on Our New AI...","author":"@joshm on Twitter","date":"2025.05.16","url":"https://twitter.com/joshm/status/1922639539295621484"},{"id":890245676,"text":"Our goal at browsercompany has always been to build a successor to the browser. One that feels personal.  We called it an “Internet Computer” in our first vid in ‘22. \n\nLast year we said the tech arrived to finally unseat Chrome, and that soon everyone will build an AI browser.","title":"An Update on Our New AI...","author":"@joshm on Twitter","date":"2025.05.16","url":"https://twitter.com/joshm/status/1922639537462825459"},{"id":890245675,"text":"Quick note on Arc: I know many of you are disappointed it’s not our focus. But I promise you Dia and Arc will unify more than you can see today. On the docket:\n\n- AI-native take on Arc’s spaces & folders\n- Arc’s Air Traffic Control but automatic\n- More of Arc’s greatest hits","title":"An Update on Our New AI...","author":"@joshm on Twitter","date":"2025.05.16","url":"https://twitter.com/joshm/status/1922639535986319855"},{"id":890245674,"text":"Finally: we’re dialing-up the craft details to make you feel something when using Dia. Alpha version we tested was rough by design. Brittle, minimal, and stripped down to prove one thing: utility.\n\nNow that we’re gearing up to ship for real we're bringing in Browser Co flair! <video controls><source src=\" type=\"application/x-mpegURL\"><source src=\" type=\"video/mp4\"><source src=\" type=\"video/mp4\"><source src=\" type=\"video/mp4\"><source src=\" type=\"video/mp4\"><source src=\" type=\"video/mp4\">Your browser does not support the video tag.</video>","title":"An Update on Our New AI...","author":"@joshm on Twitter","date":"2025.05.16","url":"https://twitter.com/joshm/status/1922639534170223079"},{"id":890245673,"text":"1. Smart History: your everyday browsing makes Dia better the more you use it (private memory)\n\n2. Vertical AI apps: package context, prompts, models, personalization into vertical assistants\n\n3. Personalization: auto-customize your own system prompt just by browsing normally","title":"An Update on Our New AI...","author":"@joshm on Twitter","date":"2025.05.16","url":"https://twitter.com/joshm/status/1922639532308021304"},{"id":890245672,"text":"Up next we'll onboard Arc members who want to try Dia, and then GA in a few months.\n\nBut first we have work to do (what’s the purpose of testing if you don’t act on those learnings).\n\nSpecifically, we’ve been working on tripling-down on context by adding the following to Dia:","title":"An Update on Our New AI...","author":"@joshm on Twitter","date":"2025.05.16","url":"https://twitter.com/joshm/status/1922639530248511559"},{"id":890245671,"text":"These aren’t all our features or learnings, but you get the point! Context is the core of Dia’s usefulness.\n\nWhy? In 2025:\n\n1. AI models need context to be most valuable\n2. Your tabs are your context\n3. Combining 1 & 2 unlocks something new\n\n“Okay cool, so when can I try Dia…”","title":"An Update on Our New AI...","author":"@joshm on Twitter","date":"2025.05.16","url":"https://twitter.com/joshm/status/1922639528944161065"},{"id":890245670,"text":"But the most wild stuff is when students combine the context from multiple tabs at once…\n\n- write a doc informed by one tab but written in the style of another tab (just @ mention)\n\n- transform all of your open tabs into a comparison table and report of the options\n\netc. <video controls><source src=\" type=\"application/x-mpegURL\"><source src=\" type=\"video/mp4\"><source src=\" type=\"video/mp4\"><source src=\" type=\"video/mp4\"><source src=\" type=\"video/mp4\"><source src=\" type=\"video/mp4\">Your browser does not support the video tag.</video>","title":"An Update on Our New AI...","author":"@joshm on Twitter","date":"2025.05.16","url":"https://twitter.com/joshm/status/1922639527295746183"},{"id":890245669,"text":"A more surprising learning is how unique context from our browser tabs can power up vertical AI workflows.\n\nex: Dia matches your writing style automatically, so the text it generates sounds like you and your doc (not AI slop).\n\nMore soon across coding, shopping, and more. \n\n!","title":"An Update on Our New AI...","author":"@joshm on Twitter","date":"2025.05.16","url":"https://twitter.com/joshm/status/1922639525123121269"},{"id":890245668,"text":"You can also get unique context into AI chat from within tabs too.\n\nex: Highlight text on a tab to turn into a “help me” button. Then ask your q & we’ll auto-route you to the right tool, auto-including the entire webpage in the context window.\n\n\"What's a better way to say this\" <video controls><source src=\" type=\"application/x-mpegURL\"><source src=\" type=\"video/mp4\"><source src=\" type=\"video/mp4\"><source src=\" type=\"video/mp4\"><source src=\" type=\"video/mp4\"><source src=\" type=\"video/mp4\">Your browser does not support the video tag.</video>","title":"An Update on Our New AI...","author":"@joshm on Twitter","date":"2025.05.16","url":"https://twitter.com/joshm/status/1922639523084734862"},{"id":890245667,"text":"We’ve even built secret integrations that hook deeply into web apps (can only do at browser layer given no public APIs).\n\nThis means we can bring info into the context window a human can’t see & apps can't get with screenshots.\n\nHere’s example of YouTube integration in action: \n\n!","title":"An Update on Our New AI...","author":"@joshm on Twitter","date":"2025.05.16","url":"https://twitter.com/joshm/status/1922639519762825450"},{"id":890245666,"text":"Dia’s most popular feature (so far) is chatting with your tabs.\n\nChat with a YouTube video.\n\nChat with a FigJam board.\n\nChat with Google Calendar.\n\nThe killer feature here is the automatic context from your tabs. No copy-and-pasting. No need to set context, Dia just knows. <video controls><source src=\" type=\"application/x-mpegURL\"><source src=\" type=\"video/mp4\"><source src=\" type=\"video/mp4\"><source src=\" type=\"video/mp4\"><source src=\" type=\"video/mp4\"><source src=\" type=\"video/mp4\">Your browser does not support the video tag.</video>","title":"An Update on Our New AI...","author":"@joshm on Twitter","date":"2025.05.16","url":"https://twitter.com/joshm/status/1922639517858623684"},{"id":890245665,"text":"Context is what makes AI most useful to us. But it’s cumbersome to get into an app.\n\nToday, our browsers are our context. Tabs reflect our work, studies, projects, questions we’re asking, docs we’re writing.\n\nLet's get into specifics & demos from Dia on what's working...","title":"An Update on Our New AI...","author":"@joshm on Twitter","date":"2025.05.16","url":"https://twitter.com/joshm/status/1922639516260549088"},{"id":890245664,"text":"But after testing Dia with students (even in half-finished, barebones state) it’s clear we got one big thing right:\n\nContext\n\nIn the words of OpenAI’s Michelle Pokrass: “The biggest bottleneck in AI isn’t the model’s capabilities — it’s getting enough relevant context.”\n\n!","title":"An Update on Our New AI...","author":"@joshm on Twitter","date":"2025.05.16","url":"https://twitter.com/joshm/status/1922639514201174226"},{"id":890245663,"text":"First things first: I was wrong about so much. So much\n\n1. chat actually is a great interface, not a bug\n\n2. computer use models were not as good as expected\n\n3. getting memory right is really hard\n\n(I’m saying “I” here b/c not everyone on team agreed with me)","title":"An Update on Our New AI...","author":"@joshm on Twitter","date":"2025.05.16","url":"https://twitter.com/joshm/status/1922639512011743486"},{"id":890245662,"text":"Btw the point of this isn't to convince you of anything. We’ve always believed in building in public, but needed time to shape Dia’s vision. Now that puzzle pieces are clicking, time to go back to sharing for those who are curious.\n\nHere are the takeaways from early testing:","title":"An Update on Our New AI...","author":"@joshm on Twitter","date":"2025.05.16","url":"https://twitter.com/joshm/status/1922639510417916288"},{"id":890245661,"text":"An update on our new AI browser, Dia:\n\nWe just wrapped alpha testing with thousands of college students. Felt like the perfect moment to share a raw browsercompany update on what’s been going on (including demos). So much to catch you up on…\n\n!","title":"An Update on Our New AI...","author":"@joshm on Twitter","date":"2025.05.16","url":"https://twitter.com/joshm/status/1922639507033149597"},{"id":890153747,"text":"创业公司的路演，大多是浪费时间。产品的验证来自于与用户交流和迭代，而不是打动评委。","title":"科技爱好者周刊（第 348 期）：李飞飞，从移民到 Ai 明星","author":"阮一峰的网络日志","date":"2025.05.16","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jvbqphqb3mz65er2cmy7bhyd"},{"id":889904807,"text":"我们创造的每一种工具都蕴含着超越其自身的意义","title":"棱镜通讯 No.109 尼尔·波兹曼（Neil Postman）","author":"太隐","date":"2025.05.15","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jvadtgxvgarpv5nv7qgj0ny9"},{"id":889902923,"text":"个体的意义坐标体系遭到了破坏，他们为了应对和抵挡各种不确定性，把寻求问题的方向重新指向了命运。在这种情况下，“命运”提供的解决问题的思路可分为两类：一是提供精神安抚和心理建设的资源，化解焦虑，成为个体意义系统的“工具箱”；二是解构比较，帮助个体认识到人与人之间的差异，肯定差异和个体的价值，从而为由线性进步观所带来的生存性焦虑提供“缓冲阀”。","title":"为什么越来越多的年轻人开始“拥抱玄学”","author":"邢婷婷","date":"2025.05.15","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jvadgcv35z55xj261avv6kc4"},{"id":889902892,"text":"“稳定”不再被认为是优点或优势，它更大程度上意味着无趣、呆板、胆小而缺乏冒险精神，不具备应变的能力。为了适应线性进步观，人们需要具备若干知识、技能、判断力，以备不时之需、应对各种突如其来的变化和机遇。","title":"为什么越来越多的年轻人开始“拥抱玄学”","author":"邢婷婷","date":"2025.05.15","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jvadfzn5zhcy596jeavajmye"},{"id":889902678,"text":"这种“双重脱嵌”也是当前中国青年在流动过程中所面临的一个普遍的问题。在“脱嵌”的情境中，个体主义倾向日趋明显，权威在指导个体行为和选择的作用下降，既有的经验体系对青年人面临的种种新情况的解释力和参考价值都出现了局限性，个体时常面临着找不到认同感、意义缺失的境遇。\n\n在这种情况下，命理信仰在青年人当中的兴起可以看作是在“脱嵌”状态下解决个体的归属和意义感的一种尝试。","title":"为什么越来越多的年轻人开始“拥抱玄学”","author":"邢婷婷","date":"2025.05.15","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jvadf0qwkdq165n69zfh1g6p"},{"id":889902651,"text":"这种流动给个人带来的影响是双向的，个人在一定程度上获得了流动的自主性，选择的空间增大、机会增多。但是，在流动的进程中，个体从故乡到他乡，制度的藩篱、文化的隔膜、认同的区隔，这些都会给个体的身份认同带来种种困难，造成碎片化的倾向。","title":"为什么越来越多的年轻人开始“拥抱玄学”","author":"邢婷婷","date":"2025.05.15","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jvadeh2c77z57k2mexa9vwbf"},{"id":889902520,"text":"在社会的变迁与发展进程中，面对日益复杂的现实生活，个体对于利弊得失一时衡量不清、自身感受与外界期待发生冲突，因此产生了不确定性和无助感，造成了个体的焦虑，占卜则为青年人的选择和决定提供了支持的依据。","title":"为什么越来越多的年轻人开始“拥抱玄学”","author":"邢婷婷","date":"2025.05.15","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jvadc4h1kskzf2hp5hdm3ndy"},{"id":887611983,"text":"BongoCat 是一个可爱的互动桌面宠物应用，让你的桌面充满乐趣！","title":"Ayangweb/BongoCat","author":"github.com","date":"2025.05.09","url":"https://readwise.io/open/887611983"},{"id":887509195,"text":"人们在夜晚和周末所做的事情，代表了世界上所有未充分利用的时间和精力。安德鲁·陈《冷启动问题","title":"科技爱好者周刊（第 347 期）：冷启动的破解之道","author":"阮一峰的网络日志","date":"2025.05.09","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jtss6esemjqvh8bx5smvh9ef"},{"id":887509105,"text":"（1）拓展你对可能性的感知。所有事情都是可能的。\n\n（2）容忍模棱两可。有些事情是不确定的，说不清是好是坏，是对是错，要容忍这样的事情。\n\n（3）经常自嘲。永远不要忘记，无论你多么确定，你都有可能犯错。\n\n（4）要关心什么是对的，不要关心谁对谁错。\n\n（5）一旦发现自己错了，不要放过，也不要不承认。\n\n（6）懂得谦逊和原谅他人。","title":"科技爱好者周刊（第 347 期）：冷启动的破解之道","author":"阮一峰的网络日志","date":"2025.05.09","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01jtss4e61egkrgcyav8vsc3h0"},{"id":718193336,"text":"分享一种体验、一个画面、一个氛围、一个观点，乃至一个故事，皆是如此。有一些只有你才关心的生活的细微，有一些只有你捕捉到的瞬间，你只有把它呈现与分享出来，它才会被人看见，这就是你带给世界的礼物。","title":"创作的意义","author":"夜猫日记","date":"2024.05.11","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01hxk4vqs2n6pm2dtsa8pfqdj6"},{"id":718193331,"text":"现在这个启示就像闪电一样，劈开了迷雾： 「将自己独特的视角，呈现给别人，让原本可能看不见的东西通过我被他人看见。」","title":"创作的意义","author":"夜猫日记","date":"2024.05.11","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01hxk4vkbkbggety9xaj8w90hw"},{"id":718193327,"text":"使原本可能看不见的东西通过你被他人看见。 ——法国著名导演 罗伯特·布列松","title":"创作的意义","author":"夜猫日记","date":"2024.05.11","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01hxk4vbtckj4g0jjqpmecsw2c"},{"id":718193325,"text":"我认为创作就是把这一刻，把自己眼中的“太好了”的瞬间，通过某种形式、某种媒介传达给别人。","title":"创作的意义","author":"夜猫日记","date":"2024.05.11","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01hxk4v61bbnq00zbhxc9rccrt"},{"id":717595500,"text":"科技行业的一切，核心都是利润，而不是其他任何事情。因此，你需要尽快推出新产品或新服务，这样才可能产生利润。这意味着尽量使用更多的抽象层、更多的自动化、更少的人员，结果就是开发者越来越缺乏对技术的深入理解。我们使用了太多的抽象层次","title":"科技爱好者周刊（第 299 期）：ai 的关键是语料","author":"阮一峰的网络日志","date":"2024.05.10","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01hxg2ejtkcp6tqbq0xc7byp2h"},{"id":717595492,"text":"我们做的许多不想做的事情，实际上很容易开始做，比如很容易开始喝酒，或者很容易打开抖音。\n\n如果你想停止做这些事，首先就是要设法增加障碍，让自己很难开始做它们。出现就是成功的75%","title":"科技爱好者周刊（第 299 期）：ai 的关键是语料","author":"阮一峰的网络日志","date":"2024.05.10","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01hxg2e3qqcgq8naesx5ymx01b"},{"id":717595392,"text":"Apple 的广告片中，那些被液压机压碎的象征人类文明的物品，无疑是一种强烈的视觉冲击。这冲击背后，也是一种极端的 “Think Different” 理念。但是，Different 不应该是对传统的否定，真正的 creative 应该是在尊重和继承传统的基础上，提出新的解决方案。","title":"老用户的失望","author":"槿呈Goidea","date":"2024.05.10","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01hxg2ag3veh6az6gdjvtz2041"},{"id":717595383,"text":"在这个快速变化的世界中，每一个人都是文明的参与者和创造者。我们选择使用的每一项技术，不仅仅是生活工具的选择，更是文化价值观的体现。","title":"老用户的失望","author":"槿呈Goidea","date":"2024.05.10","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01hxg2a6mvt375rxz613k8ye9b"},{"id":717595380,"text":"当这种影响力开始向「定义一切」倾斜时，请务必警惕。科技应该是开放的、包容的，它应该鼓励创造性思维，而不是将所有人都框定在一个统一的思维模式中。","title":"老用户的失望","author":"槿呈Goidea","date":"2024.05.10","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01hxg2a07caxrr51c1e877y0fr"},{"id":716738903,"text":"为什么我们要始终保持哲学思考？因为无论是关心宇宙，关心自然，还是关心自己乃至自己和其他人关系，其实都是我们作为有理性的人内在灵魂的冲动。而这样的冲动，在你的生命当中，可能会在某一个时刻，特别是当你被为之奋斗的世界搞得厌烦的时候，不期而然地走出来。这就是你需要哲学思考的时候。","title":"哲学思考的根本意义在于走出洞穴｜书院课","author":"1mo 广东清远岭南书院","date":"2024.05.08","url":"https://readwise.io/open/716738903"},{"id":716738851,"text":"哲学思考源于一种惊异，源于我们每一个有理性的存在者的形而上学的渴望。","title":"哲学思考的根本意义在于走出洞穴｜书院课","author":"1mo 广东清远岭南书院","date":"2024.05.08","url":"https://readwise.io/open/716738851"},{"id":711603422,"text":"敏捷开发有一个问题，就是它要求\"新的冲刺在上一个冲刺结束后立即开始。\"\n\n有了这个规则，程序员就陷入了永远冲刺的陷阱。永远冲刺","title":"科技爱好者周刊（第 298 期）：轮到硬件工程师吃香了","author":"阮一峰的网络日志","date":"2024.04.26","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01hwchyfzm0day426vf5mwtcjc"},{"id":711603019,"text":"特斯拉的市值高得离谱，达到4800亿美元，2022年总收入810亿美元，市盈率36倍。\n\n相比之下，美国最大的汽车公司通用汽车的市值500亿美元，2022年总收入为1720亿美元，市盈率6倍。\n\n特斯拉的问题在于，市场把它当成 Meta 和谷歌那样的科技公司，但它实际上是一家汽车公司。一旦市场开始认清这一点，股价就不可避免地下跌了。Hacker News 读者，评论特斯拉的股价不断下跌","title":"科技爱好者周刊（第 298 期）：轮到硬件工程师吃香了","author":"阮一峰的网络日志","date":"2024.04.26","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01hwchxh2aa7vgyqevqr4tapty"},{"id":711053433,"text":"李梦霁在《允许一切发生》里说，“人间是一个巨大的游乐场，我们在其间闯荡，不问前程。只为体验，只为成长，只为尽兴一场”。","title":"俗世奇人金圣叹","author":"太隐","date":"2024.04.25","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01hw9g6k6n2gr56zv9cgcxaebn"},{"id":710329021,"text":"这甚至让快乐变得与消费无关，你可以享受咖啡，享受烘焙，享受 fine dining，享受旅游，享受潜水，它们各自有各自的快乐。但如果你购买或消费这些，只是为了发朋友圈，那么实际上你只获得了一种快乐就是朋友圈的快乐——因此，甚至出现了前两年的「拼下午茶」的现象。\n\n然而，朋友圈就那么几个人，大家点赞的数量有上限，最后会不可避免地开始追求「买更好的工具晒」「想办法经历更特殊的事迹」这样「讨好式」的行为，因为重复原来的动作已经无法在朋友圈引来点赞了，无法满足自己对于「点赞数」这个生活的 KPI 的追求了，这些动作不能让自己产生多巴胺了，只能升级了。\n\n这时，目标导向会为我们带来另一个生活中有毒的思维方式：增长成瘾。\n\n工作可以有结果，但是生活是没有尽头的，用自己给自己定 KPI 的方式生活，最后就会陷入「需要花钱体验更新奇的事情」这样的循环之中。\n\n我们陷入了一种怪圈，作为劳动者在公司 996 去卷，然后作为消费者下班去花钱购买别人 996 卷出来的商品与服务。而这些商品与服务无论是否能为人们带来快乐，作为消费者的我都不再在意，因为我既无时间也无兴趣体验快乐的过程，而只希望能够有一个快乐的结果。于是在短暂的感官刺激与社交虚荣之后，就又要继续去 996 赚更多钱以再次购买由他人血汗制造出的虚假快乐。\n\n陷入了这种消费陷阱的精致白领们，其实和喜欢充钱玩「是朋友就砍我一刀」页游的煤老板们没有什么本质区别，只不过前者的陷阱更加隐蔽。","title":"现代打工人如何获得幸福？","author":"评论尸","date":"2024.07.29","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01hw4sg6c6pqx8t60jpkjgsbrm"},{"id":710328989,"text":"小红书这几年的异军突起恰恰证明了这一点。在朋友圈小范围地晒已经无法满足大家的欲望了，必须在公开场所晒，比谁更精致，比谁更懂生活，实际上生活不需要懂。我们每个人都应该天然地会生活。\n\n这种现象最糟糕的点在于，外化生活的快乐，会破坏体验过程的机会，破坏生活的快乐本身。这会让地球上数十万种花钱和不花钱的快乐，简化为「购买」和「分享」两个行为，并且不可持续。","title":"现代打工人如何获得幸福？","author":"评论尸","date":"2024.04.23","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01hw4sfnxayqq4qywz73g15vqq"},{"id":710328126,"text":"!","title":"现代打工人如何获得幸福？","author":"评论尸","date":"2024.04.23","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01hw4s3jkssb60bekxk8j73k61"},{"id":710327252,"text":"在完全理解了这张图之后，你会发现幸福是一个平衡性问题，它并不是一个线性函数，而更像是一个线性函数通过积分所得的面积。\n\n而在这个平衡性问题中，有两件事是对我们一生的幸福总量十分重要的：一个是工作，另一个是学习（工作准备）。\n\n这意味着，你至少不应该把钱作为衡量工作的第一位，而是把快乐本身放在衡量工作的第一位。\n\n在我们过往职场对工作的选择中，排名第一位的要么是钱，要么是钱途，往后排可能是工作的困难程度，距离家的远近，工作环境是否优越等等，兴趣似乎很少出现在中国人择业的首选项里。\n\n然而，当你想明白你一生最好的时光，必将投入在工作中时，你就会明白：如果想要让整个人生的大部分时段快乐起来，你就不可能去做一份痛苦的工作，来换取剩下的快乐时光。","title":"现代打工人如何获得幸福？","author":"评论尸","date":"2024.04.23","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01hw4s0rqe9szyhk62bb8ywwr6"},{"id":710323464,"text":"在很多关于远离低质量娱乐，劝说人们应当自律，延迟满足类的进步教鸡汤里。都会试图描述这样一种场景：\n\n上班劳累了一周，本知道应当去学习一下、见见朋友、搞搞副业或做一些高质量的娱乐，但不知不觉中却躺在床上刷了两整天的抖音或打了几十盘王者。到了周日的晚上才恍然大悟，懊悔不已。\n\n接下来，进步教鸡汤往往会针对这个场景提出一些改进措施，帮助你放弃抖音和王者这种低质量娱乐，追寻一些「高质量娱乐」或「延迟满足」。\n\n但在 2.1 一节中我们已经知道了，幸福和快乐的最重要量度其实是时间，因此你也许一眼就可以看出延迟满足理论的缺陷——\n\n我在所谓的低质量娱乐中度过了一个愉快的周末，仅在周末结束的时候有一些懊悔。而在延迟满足模式下，度过的可能是一个忙碌但并不愉快的周末，而这种忙碌究竟在何时带给我何种快乐是完全无法预测的。\n\n「低质量娱乐」给我带来了 2 天的幸福，「对低质量娱乐的反思」带给了我 2 小时的抑郁。\n\n这意味着，我需要解决的恰恰不是「低质量娱乐」，而是「低质量娱乐有害」这种使我周日晚上感到愧疚的社会建构。","title":"现代打工人如何获得幸福？","author":"评论尸","date":"2024.04.23","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01hw4rpgyabgq5gge1gyje25s3"},{"id":710322906,"text":"20 世纪 60 年代，美国斯坦福大学心理学教授沃尔特·米歇尔做了一个时至今日仍被不断复述的实验：让一些孩子在一个单调的小房间里，看着一块棉花糖。实验者告诉孩子，如果在他回来之前，棉花糖没有被吃掉，就可以额外获得一块棉花糖。\n\n一些孩子很快放弃，而另外一些孩子成功等到了第二块糖，根据跟踪调查发现，那些成功抵御住立刻吃掉一块糖欲望的孩子，在之后的成绩、就业、处理人际关系上，都比另外那些孩子都要优秀。\n\n但这个实验，在 2018 年的另一篇论文1中几乎被推翻。\n\n纽约大学的研究者泰勒·沃茨，加州大学的雷格·邓肯和全浩南，将原始的延迟满足实验样本扩大到了 10 倍（900 人），使孩子的人口学特征更加多样化（包含不同种族），并对孩子原本的家庭环境做出了变量控制。最终的结果发现，拥有延迟满足能力的群体比没有这一能力的群体只增加了 10% 的成功概率，这远低于推导出「延迟满足」能力的那份研究。\n\n其中的一种猜测是，原始研究中延迟满足能力与成就之间并非因果性，而是相关性。那些家境好的孩子，在小时更容易抵制一颗糖的诱惑。而等到他们长大后，更容易成功也是因为他们家境好，而不是因为他们懂得延迟满足。\n\n如果你曾是一个信奉延迟满足的人，在读到这段之后可能会有一种强烈的幻灭感。但如果你真的能从延迟满足中获得满足的人，就会觉得这个新的消息对你的生活没什么影响。","title":"现代打工人如何获得幸福？","author":"评论尸","date":"2024.04.23","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01hw4rg3fkrmyvnx0vhadzrjmz"},{"id":710322891,"text":"所以，实际上没有所谓的低质量快乐，与低质量幸福。人生的幸福，是一生中每个时刻幸福度的积分，而幸福度是一种只与「当下」有关的主观体验。","title":"现代打工人如何获得幸福？","author":"评论尸","date":"2024.04.23","url":"https://read.readwise.io/read/01hw4rffm13dbq0p945nva1vzn"}]}</script>
